text: A Sydney funnel-web spider or Atrax robustus is a species of funnel-web spider. Their bite is very serious and venomous and has killed 13 people since 1927. It is found in Sydney, Australia. The funnel-web spider can be substantially larger than a 50 cent piece. ==Other websites == *Sydney funnel- web spider at the Museum of Australia Category:Mygalomorphae
title: Sydney funnel-web spider
